up and&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:10pt;\">feedback)&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Final Oral Assessment - 30%. Mr. Lin would like students to make a live presentation (group) talking about a topic from Unit 1 to 5 or a subject students are interested in. Students should speak for at least 1 minute. (2-member group = 2 minutes; 3-member group = 3 minutes). Final class feedback.&nbsp;</span></p>", "<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Review.</span>"], "授業計画1": "Students at times you may need a laptop computer or a portable device with wifi connection. Be sure you can access Luna, KWIC, Microsoft 365, Microsoft Teams, Slack, your KGU e-mail address, and have a Google account.", "授業外学習2": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"margin:0cm;font-size:medium;font-family:;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;background-image:none;background-position:0% 0%;background-size:auto;background-repeat:repeat;background-attachment:scroll;background-origin:padding-box;background-clip:border-box;\">Students are required to prepare for class and when appropriate review. Students are required to bring their textbook, a pen or pencil, paper, and a dictionary to class. Expect to spend about 30 minutes each week previewing and reviewing the textbook contents. Expect to spend an additional 1 hour every other week or 30 minutes each week completing homework assignments.&nbsp;</span></p>"}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["Time Zones 3A (Third Edition) by David Bohlke and Andrew Boon."], "教科書/Required texts1": ["David Bohlke and Andrew Boon.", "Time Zones 3A (Third Edition)", "National Geographic Learning", "2021 年", "9780357426753", ""], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": ["Please follow your school directions."], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students1": ["各授業科目は、各学部・研究科の定めるディプロマ・ポリシー（DP）・カリキュラム・ポリシー（CP）に基づき、カリキュラム上に配置されています。DP・CPを意識して本授業科目の学修を進めることで、各学部・研究科の期待する能力が養成されます。各学部・研究科のDP、CPや教育課程表（授業科目一覧等）は、下記リンクこちらに掲載していますので学修計画の参考にしてください。https://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/reference?typeCd=0&amp;cabinetId=557&amp;directLink=1※kwicへのリンクとなります（在学生のみ閲覧可）"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["授業中試験／In-class examination (03)", "40 %", "Student grades will be based on the criteria listed below."], "成績評価Grading2": ["授業外学修課題／Assignment, homework required outside class (06)", "20 %", "Student grades will be based on the criteria listed below."], "成績評価Grading3": ["プレゼンテーション・発表／Presentation (07)", "30 %", "Student grades will be based on the criteria listed below."], "成績評価Grading4": ["授業への参加度（自発性、積極性、主体性、等）／In-class participation,contribution (09)", "10 %", "Student grades will be based on the criteria listed below."], "成績評価Grading5": ["備考　Note Class Participation – 10%Assignments – 15%On-Demand Review Task&nbsp;–&nbsp;5%Quiz #1 – 20%Quiz #2 – 20%Final Oral Assessment&nbsp;–&nbsp;30%Total – 100%Average Grades For The Department&nbsp;–&nbsp;70&nbsp;–&nbsp;75.The student's grade will be based on quizzes, writing assignments, and oral presentations. No final exam will be given during the exam period. Those students who miss five or more classes during the term will receive 0 points for this course.&nbsp;"], "備考Note0": ["Students are expected to speak English only in class. You will not pass the course if you miss more than five (5) classes. If you are more than five (5) minutes late for class, you will be considered late. Three (3) lates will equal one (1) absence. An absence or tardy is only excused when documentation is provided by Kyomu (Academic Affairs Office). Mr. Lin's e-mail is fts77833@kwansei.ac.jp. All homework will be facilitated on the Microsoft Teams App through Assignments. Students will submit their homework assignments through MS Teams Assignments. Homework should always be submitted (usually at the beginning of class) on the day that it’s due. If there are exceptions, Mr. Lin will let students know.&nbsp;Mr. Lin will explain how to submit in class. All tasks of the class should be completed by their due dates. Mr. Lin does not allow students to mass submit (a semester's worth of work) at the end of classes or after the end of classes.Please download the Microsoft Team App on your phone and PC. Please download the Slack app on your phone and PC. The URLs will be updated before the 2nd class. Register with your KGU ID and PW.&nbsp;Please make sure you have a Google or Gmail Account. Using a personal Google account is fine. We will be using Google Forms."], "備考Note1": ["TimeZones 3A.JPG", "Your textbook"], "備考Note2": ["TimeZones 3A (2).JPG", "Your textbook ISBN"], "備考Note3": ["English 1b 5 Microsoft Team Link"], "備考Note4": ["English 1b 5 Slack Link"], "備考Note5": ["2026年01月29日 01時13分16秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "春学期／Spring", "水曜３時限／Wednesday 3", "春学期／Spring", "経－７"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "【100】英語Iｂ　５／English Ib", "管理部署": 4, "単位数": 1, "担当者": "リン　マイケル　Ｐ．（LIN MICHAEL P.） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "予備登録", "開講期": 1, "時限1": 16, "評価1": 2, "評価2": 7, "評価3": 4, "評価4": 5, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\nClass Participation – 10%\nAssignments – 15%\nOn-Demand Review Task – 5%\nQuiz #1 – 20%\nQuiz #2 – 20%\nFinal Oral Assessment – 30%\nTotal – 100%\n\nAverage Grades For The Department – 70 – 75.\n\nThe student's grade will be based on quizzes, writing assignments, and oral presentations. No final exam will be given during the exam period. Those students who miss five or more classes during the term will receive 0 points for this course. "}